### File Structure
```
RealEstate/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── property_search.html
│   ├── property_details.html
│   ├── property_inquiry.html
│   ├── my_inquiries.html
│   ├── my_favorites.html
│   ├── agents.html
│   └── locations.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (property and agent images if any)
│
└── data/
    ├── properties.txt
    ├── locations.txt
    ├── inquiries.txt
    ├── favorites.txt
    └── agents.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file that handles routing, data processing, and business logic for all eight pages. It reads from and writes to the local text files in the 'data' directory. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here for simplicity and maintainability.

- templates/
  Contains all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the eight pages defined in the requirements:
  - dashboard.html: Dashboard page layout and elements.
  - property_search.html: Property search and filter interface.
  - property_details.html: Detailed property information display.
  - property_inquiry.html: Form for submitting property inquiries.
  - my_inquiries.html: Display and management of user inquiries.
  - my_favorites.html: Display and management of favorite properties.
  - agents.html: Real estate agents directory and search.
  - locations.html: Featured locations with sorting and navigation.

- static/
  Contains static assets used by the web pages:
  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
  - images/: Folder for property and agent images if applicable.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
  - properties.txt: Property listings data.
  - locations.txt: Location information data.
  - inquiries.txt: Property inquiries data.
  - favorites.txt: Favorite properties data.
  - agents.txt: Real estate agents data.
```
This structure supports a clean separation of concerns, easy maintenance, and straightforward deployment for the 'RealEstate' Python web application using local text files for data storage.
